1
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,160
Hello, Director.

2
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:33,759
What's your name?

3
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,800
Jiang Xiaomei.

4
00:01:35,759 --> 00:01:37,000
Jiang Xiaomei.

5
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,200
Nice name.

6
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:43,039
Have you worked as an assistant before?

7
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:44,759
No.

8
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,440
It's okay.

9
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,080
Very good.

10
00:01:48,479 --> 00:01:49,610
Please, have a seat.

11
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,130
What happened to your foot?

12
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,920
The shoes don't fit well.

13
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,480
Which one?

14
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:09,400
The left... left foot.

15
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,970
Indeed, they don't fit.

16
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:23,840
Lao'er.

17
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,400
Mr. Xiao.

18
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:28,610
Have them get the car ready.

19
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,720
Where to, Mr. Xiao?

20
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:30,920
To the shopping mall.

21
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,920
Okay.

22
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,000
We're going to buy shoes.

23
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,320
Thank you.

24
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,440
Mr. Wu, this is freshly washed ore.

25
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,500
Check the quality.

26
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:58,640
Gang, regarding you kidnapping Mr. Xiao...

27
00:02:58,640 --> 00:02:59,600
Mr. Xiao said,

28
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,160
we can't buy your ore anymore.

29
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:03,280
Mr. Wu, the police already cleared me.

30
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,940
I didn't kidnap Xiao Tianman.

31
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,280
Gang, we're all on the same side.

32
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,200
Stop lying to yourself.

33
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:13,320
Sorry, please leave.

34
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,280
Mr. Wu.

35
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,040
Please help me out.

36
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,240
I really can't.

37
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,200
I'll give you a thirty percent kickback.

38
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,600
It's not about the money... Fifty percent.

39
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:30,010
Fifty percent? You'd be working for nothing.

40
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,880
Mr. Wu, I really need the money.

41
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,040
Please help me.

42
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:37,560
Fine, I'll help you this once.

43
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:48,960
Eighty.

44
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,360
Thank you, Mr. Wu.

45
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,040
Next.

46
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:29,640
New face, huh?

47
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,450
Which village are you from?

48
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,540
The neighboring village.

49
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,640
Helping my husband sell ore.

50
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,360
Neighboring village...

51
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,800
Stop right there!

52
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,840
Follow her!

53
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:08,840
Stop!

54
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:15,690
Where is she?

55
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,040
You two go ahead. Go.

56
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,920
Are you crazy?

57
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:34,040
Why are they chasing you?

58
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,320
What is wrong with you?

59
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,400
I just saved you. Not even a thank you?

60
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:41,560
Thank you.

61
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,060
Where are you from?

62
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,720
The neighboring village.

63
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,780
I'm here helping my husband sell ore.

64
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:48,240
Neighboring village...

65
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:50,480
No one from the neighboring village has skin as soft as yours.

66
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:52,320
Do you know who those people were?

67
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,440
Xiao Tianman's men.

68
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,170
Do you know who Xiao Tianman is?

69
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,520
He's the local tyrant around here.

70
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,640
I'm telling you, it's dangerous.

71
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:58,400
Got it.

72
00:05:58,720 --> 00:05:59,520
Hey.

73
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:07,100
Are people from the neighboring village this rude?

74
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:23,800
Director Xiao.

75
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,400
These numbers aren't right.

76
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,970
Take it, take it. Here, here, here.

77
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,520
Everyone, everyone.

78
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,520
Please calm down.

79
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,440
Step back first. Step back.

80
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:33,170
Let me say a few words to you all.

81
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:36,000
You might have already noticed this.

82
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:38,680
The relocation fee you've received,

83
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,159
compared to what you were supposed to get,

84
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:43,080
there is a difference.

85
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,720
Let me explain.

86
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:49,560
Shanshui Group should have

87
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,760
paid this relocation fee immediately.

88
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,240
But my hands are tied.

89
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:57,159
They keep delaying the payment.

90
00:06:57,159 --> 00:06:58,620
I completely understand.

91
00:06:59,159 --> 00:07:00,560
Everyone has a life to live.

92
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,020
And everyone needs money.

93
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,520
I really had no choice.

94
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:06,120
The partial payment you received now,

95
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:09,680
is every cent I could scrape together from the mine's funds,

96
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,840
to pay you all first.

97
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:14,760
To help you tide over the immediate crisis.

98
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:15,920
Honestly,

99
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,520
where your future lies,

100
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,000
even I don't know.

101
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,580
But there is one thing,

102
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,680
I, Xiao Tianman, promise you today.

103
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,800
Whatever I can do for you,

104
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:30,680
I will do it without hesitation.

105
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,800
Whatever benefits I can fight for,

106
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:34,680
I will fight for them. Okay?

107
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:37,240
Okay!

108
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,340
You're the best, Mr. Xiao!

109
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:42,080
Thank you, everyone. Thank you.

110
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,340
Distribute the money.

111
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,490
Come on, one by one. Line up, everyone.

112
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,000
Isn't this Yang Gang?

113
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,060
Shanshui Group's lapdog.

114
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:11,090
You have the nerve to come for the relocation fee?

115
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,360
What thick skin.

116
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:30,640
Yang Gang.

117
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,400
Situ Hongtang.

118
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,770
Head of restructuring at Shanshui Group.

119
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,960
That rude woman from the neighboring village.

120
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,840
So you're from Shanshui Group.

121
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,890
What do you want?

122
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,000
I have something to ask you.

123
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,770
Can we talk somewhere else?

124
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,200
Gang.

125
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:03,240
How do you know that Situ whatever-her-name-is?

126
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,380
Doesn't matter how I know her.

127
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,480
The point is whether she can help us.

128
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,400
I'm here to help you.

129
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,520
Let's play a game.

130
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:20,960
Whoever scores a basket,

131
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,600
gets to ask the other a question.

132
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,530
But you have to answer truthfully.

133
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,600
You in?

134
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,600
Sure.

135
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,360
The Dayang Village Mine loses money every year.

136
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,480
Does it have anything to do with Xiao Tianman?

137
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,360
What do you mean 'anything to do with'?

138
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,760
Xiao Tianman is stealing from the company.

139
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,760
He steals and sells the ore privately.

140
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:51,760
Making a fortune.

141
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,800
Xiao Tianman decided who got laid off.

142
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,040
Who else?

143
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:03,480
Xiao Tianman only kept his cronies.

144
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,530
Everyone else got laid off.

145
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,960
I heard on the day production stopped,

146
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:17,490
he distributed relocation fees to everyone.

147
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,560
Do you think that was enough?

148
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,980
The villagers are still protesting.

149
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,280
Then how do they survive?

150
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,120
Farming.

151
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,880
Odd jobs.

152
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,920
Stealing ore.

153
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:38,820
Which one are you? That's the next question.

154
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,520
My turn.

155
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,000
Go ahead.

156
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,160
Ms. Situ.

157
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,880
I really want to ask,

158
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,000
about your Shanshui Group,

159
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,970
coming here for the reform.

160
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,810
What kind of reform is this?

161
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:12,200
Shanshui Group contracted Dayang Village Mine.

162
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,960
The goal is to restructure the organization with a new system

163
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,360
and improve efficiency.

164
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:22,000
Does improving efficiency mean taking all the old miners

165
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,130
and firing them all?

166
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:24,240
Miss Situ,

167
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,600
let me ask you something.

168
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:28,130
Do you think the losses at Dayang Village Mine

169
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,880
are because we miners aren't hardworking

170
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,010
or diligent enough?

171
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,000
Is that it?

172
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,240
Have you ever considered

173
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:38,280
that mining is the only thing we've known all our lives?

174
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,880
Without this job,

175
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,530
how are we supposed to survive?

176
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,000
So,

177
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,770
are you actually here to help us

178
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,240
or to hurt us?

179
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,960
You ask too many questions.
